[6] Cholera - India (Karnataka State)
Date: Thu 15 Feb 2018 0:13 IST
Source: Deccan Herald [edited]
http://www.deccanherald.com/content/659544/villagers-died-cholera-confirms-dc.html


Deputy Commissioner M Lokesh said 4 residents of Maidolalu village in Bhadravathi taluk died of cholera. Speaking to reporters here on [Wed 7 Feb 2018], he said stool and water samples sent to district laboratory had confirmed the outbreak of cholera in the village. Consumption of contaminated water is the cause of cholera. Water supply through existing pipeline is stopped and a new pipeline will be soon installed. Treated water is being supplied to the village through tankers, he said.

Lokesh said residents complained of gastroenteritis on [Sun 11 Feb 2018] at Maidolalu village and were admitted to McGann and a private hospital. Out of 54 cases reported, 4 adults died of cholera. He said a training camp for home guard aspirants was held in the village between [Mon 29 Jan and Thu 8 Feb 2018]. Due to the lack of adequate toilets, the home guards opted for open defecation. This might have led to water contamination.

The deputy commissioner said he had not received any letter from the National Human Rights Commission seeking a report on the incident.

--
